			<TR>
			<TD BGCOLOR=#182B42 COLSPAN=2><FONT SIZE=2 FACE=ARIAL>
			Ok finally some info on how to GET this item. It drops in the house in the Estate of Unrest. It's difficult to describe in text the path on how to get to that room, but it mainly involves going up from the 'ghoul room' near the entrance and is above the room where the Undead Barkeep spawns.<br>
<br>
There are three spawns in the room, Undead Knight of Unrest or his PH spawn in the middle, and there are two spawns off to the sides. The spawns off to the sides can be a barbed bone skeleton, skeletal monk, greater dark bone, werebat, or festering hag. The hags are by far the most dangerous, as they're wizards. The PH for the Knight is always a festering hag. I did this room easily with a druid friend when we were both 39. The trick to getting anything from unrest is to bring along a lvl 39 or higher druid who can share wolf form the entire party. Wolves are indifferent to EVERYTHING in unrest, and if you're green to the mob it won't assist on you either. <br>
<br>
About the knight himself: he's a lvl 25 or so SK, nothing special except of course he opens with harm touch like all NPC SK's. He looks like a regular skeleton, except larger. His common drop is the Bloodstained Mantle, a very nice meleer shoulder slot item, particularly when they may need SV magic, and his rare is the BS tunic.<br>
<br>
BS tunic looks like banded but tinted dark red, much like BI looks like Banded tinted black. Best look i've seen of it is on wood elf rangers IMHO. <br>
<br>
Camping the tunic for my shammy twink the spawn went like this:<br>
<br>
Knight - Mantle<br>
PH<br>
PH<br>
PH<br>
Knight - Tunic<br>
<br>
Well thats all the info I can think of right now, it's a great shammy item, more useful than a Totemic BP and probly easier to get too.<br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
<br>
- Masakari Yakikorosu<br>
Bard of 39 Songs<br>
MT<BR>
