			<TD BGCOLOR=#182B42 COLSPAN=2><FONT SIZE=2 FACE=ARIAL>
			As a merchant of sorts on the Tribunal server, I have had the opprotunity to wear a variety of different armor's, robes, and the what not in my chest slot.  After trading recently, I found myself without a BP, and found the Blood Stained Tunic, for petty sum of 150 plat.  Now lets do a bit of comparison...<br>
<br>
Bloodstained Tunic<br>
12 ac 4 agi 4 wisdom<br>
(round 250 plat max)<br>
Crystal Covered Shroud<br>
12 ac 4 str 4 wis 4  int 10sv cold<br>
(round 1k-2k plat)<br>
<br>
In this example, we have two equally imho ugly pieces of armor, with pretty similar stats.  True, the CCS is wearable by a monk, but the price difference defiently doesn't make it better then a foreman's tunic(wt. 0.0), and if you really think about the tunic is a better deal then most BP slots you will find with 4 wisdom...I'm not flaming anyone, just an opinion from someone who has watched his BP slot change from tons of things, and settled on the tunic till either he gets GEB's.<br>
<br>
~Torvald~<br>
Merchant<br>
Tribunal<br>
